The paper discusses the governance and regulation of machine learning systems, specifically in relation to data protection law. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), cybersecurity (cs.CY), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the focus on attacks on machine learning models and their implications for data protection law, cs.CR and cs.LG are the most likely categories.
